<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12114d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12114d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12114d"> 114(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> it was answered him</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Winioc <font color="green">[a neighbouring priest]</font> s&apos;aper&ccedil;ut que les magasins &agrave; c&eacute;r&eacute;ales &eacute;taient tr&egrave;s peu fournis. Ceci l&apos;&eacute;tonna, le scandalisa presque: n&apos;&eacute;tait-ce point tenter le Seigneur que de se d&eacute;sint&eacute;resser ainsi du lendemain? Il ne put s&apos;emp&ecirc;cher d&apos;en faire le reproche &agrave; son compagnon: &ldquo; Le peuple qui sert de son mieux le Cr&eacute;ateur, lui fut-il r&eacute;pondu, ne souffrira pas de la faim. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Le lendemain matin &mdash; &eacute;tait-ce un hasard? &mdash; il repassa par le m&ecirc;me endroit; la porte du magasin &eacute;tait ouverte au large et, &agrave; l&apos;int&eacute;rieur, &ocirc; surprise! s&apos;&eacute;levaient des monceaux de grains. Tout interdit, il s&apos;avance: qui donc, durant la nuit, avait amen&eacute; tant de provisions? <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> / Et Winioc, se baissant, promena sur le chemin un regard attentif: il ne d&eacute;couvrit aucun vestige qui lui r&eacute;v&eacute;l&acirc;t l&apos;intervention des hommes, et force lui fut de confesser que le Tr&egrave;s-Haut est assez puissant pour assurer &agrave; ses fid&egrave;les des vivres dans le d&eacute;sert. <br><font color="green">[Winioc [a neighbouring priest]</font> noticed that the grain warehouses were poorly stocked. This surprised him, almost scandalised him: was it not tempting the Lord to be so oblivious of the day to come? He could not stop himself from reproaching his companion: &ldquo;The people who do their best to serve their Creator&rdquo;, <mark>it was answered to him</mark>, &ldquo;will not suffer from hunger&rdquo;. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The following morning &mdash; was this by chance? &mdash; he again passed by the same place: the door of the warehouse was wide open and inside &mdash; O surprise! &mdash; heaps of grain were piled up. Dumbfounded he advanced. Who then had brought all these supplies during the night? <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> And <mark>Winioc, bending down, carefully examined the path</mark>: he could discover no signs of human intervention, and this forced him to admit that the Almighty is powerful enough to secure food for His faithful in the wilderness.] <small> <a name="STCM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#STCM"><cite title="source">Saint Colomban</cite></a> (1905) 68-9</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12117f" href="c12all.htm#c12117f">VI.C.12:117(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
